name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG GS 'Mocha'
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG GS ‘Mocha’ showcases color blocking that recalls the ‘Dark Mocha’ AJ1 from 2020. The low-top sports a white leather upper with contrasting black accents on the Swoosh and forefoot overlay. Brown nubuck construction is utilized on the heel and back tab, marked with the iconic Wings logo. A woven Nike tag adorns the breathable nylon tongue. The sneaker rests on a standard rubber cupsole, featuring stitched sidewall construction and encapsulated Air-sole cushioning.

name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG PS 'Mocha'
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG PS ‘Mocha’ features a white and black leather upper with brown nubuck construction on the heel overlay and back tab. The latter displays the iconic Wings logo, while a woven Nike tag decorates the tongue. The low-top is appointed with classic Jordan details, including a perforated toe box and a durable rubber cupsole. Underfoot, the outsole pattern features a pivot circle originally designed for the hardwood.

name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG TD 'Mocha'
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG TD ‘Mocha’ features color blocking that parallels the AJ1 ‘Dark Mocha’ from 2020. The low-top makes use of a white leather upper, contrasted by black accents on the forefoot overlay and signature Swoosh. Brown nubuck construction is utilized on the heel overlay and back tab. The latter is stamped with the iconic Wings logo, while a woven Nike tag appears on the tongue. Underfoot, a black rubber outsole provides reliable traction for growing feet.

name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (Women's)
Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Reverse Oreo'
story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 6 Retro GS ‘Reverse Oreo’ draws inspiration from the black-and-white AJ6 colorway from 2010. The legacy silhouette dons a white leather upper, contrasted by a molded black tongue and a matching black textile lining. Jumpman branding embellishes the neoprene lace cover and back heel. The midsole and molded pull tab feature white speckles against a solid black backdrop, accentuating the shoe’s cookies-and-cream design motif Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

name: Air Jordan 6 Retro PS 'Reverse Oreo'
story: Offered in pre-school sizing, the Air Jordan 6 Retro PS ‘Reverse Oreo’ presents a two-tone colorway inspired by the classic AJ6 release from 2010. Built with crisp white leather, the upper features perforated detailing and contrasting hits of black on the molded tongue and interior lining. Embroidered Jumpman branding decorates the lace cover and back heel. Anchoring the sneaker is a lightweight foam midsole, ornamented with black accents covered in white speckles.

name: Air Jordan 6 Retro TD 'Reverse Oreo'
story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro TD ‘Reverse Oreo’ takes its design cues from a black-and-white AJ6 colorway originally released in 2010. Crisp white leather is utilized on the upper, accented with perforated detailing and contrasting hits of black on the interior lining and tongue. The latter is marked with Jordan branding and an embroidered Jumpman logo. A second Jumpman icon decorates the back heel. A cushy foam midsole features white speckles against a solid black backdrop.

name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low GS 'Legend Pink'
story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low GS ‘Legend Pink’ delivers a pastel colorway of the legacy silhouette. White ballistic mesh is utilized on the upper, fortified with a pink patent leather mudguard and secured with rope laces that feed through webbing eyelets. Branding elements include a Jumpman logo and a stylized ‘23’ on the back heel. The low-top is mounted on a white Phylon midsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and a carbon fiber spring plate. A translucent rubber outsole features herringbone traction pods for reliable grip.

name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low TD 'Legend Pink'
story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low TD ‘Legend Pink’ brings pastel accents to the championship model. Rope laces feed through webbing eyelets to secure the upper, crafted from white ballistic mesh with a shiny patent leather mudguard in a soft pink finish. Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and back tab. The sneaker rests on a white foam midsole for lightweight cushioning and a comfortable ride. A translucent rubber outsole provides durable traction.

name: Wmns Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Latte'
story: The Women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Latte’ dresses the classic silhouette in color blocking that mirrors the ‘Dark Mocha’ AJ1 from 2020. Built with a crisp white base, the leather upper features black accents on the forefoot overlay and Swoosh, along with contrasting hits of dark tan on the heel and collar flap. The latter is marked with the iconic Wings logo, while a woven Nike Air tag embellishes the tongue. Underpinning the high-top is a vintage off-white rubber midsole, fitted with an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in a lightweight polyurethane wedge.

name: Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Oxidized Green'
story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Oxidized Green’ arrives in a crisp white leather upper with tonal quarter panel netting and grey molded eyelets. Contrasting green accents make their way to the support wings and back tab, marked with embossed Jumpman branding. A second Jumpman logo decorates the woven tongue tag. An additional hit of green coloring distinguishes the lightweight polyurethane midsole, featuring an exposed Air-sole unit in the heel.

name: Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'Red Taxi'
story: Built for little kids, the Air Jordan 12 Retro PS ‘Red Taxi’ adds bold pops of color to an OG-inspired white and black colorway. White tumbled leather is utilized on the upper, which is accented with radiating stitched lines and a black lizard-textured mudguard. An embroidered Jumpman logo in Gym Red adorns the tongue, matching the TPU midfoot overlay. A foam midsole offers lightweight cushioning with each step, while the rubber outsole features herringbone traction pods for superior grip.

name: Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Red Taxi'
story: The Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Red Taxi’ adds splashes of color to a familiar colorway inspired by an OG 1996 release. Crafted from tumbled white leather, the upper features radiating stitched lines and a lizard-textured mudguard in a contrasting black finish. A crimson Jumpman logo is embroidered on the tongue, matching a midfoot TPU overlay. Performance benefits include a lightweight Phylon midsole with full-length Zoom Air cushioning and a carbon fiber spring plate.

name: Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'Red Taxi'
story: The Air Jordan TD Retro PS ‘Red Taxi’ draws inspiration from an OG colorway of the championship silhouette that Michael Jordan wore during the ’96 – ’97 NBA season. Like the older shoe, the design is highlighted by a white tumbled leather upper, accented with stitched lines and fortified with a black lizard-textured mudguard. Gym Red accents make their way to the midfoot overlay and a Jumpman logo embroidered on the tongue. Underfoot, the outsole features herringbone traction pods for reliable grip.

name: Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'Red Taxi'
story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 12 Retro GS ‘Red Taxi’ takes inspiration from a classic OG colorway of the championship silhouette. Radiating stitched lines enliven the upper, crafted from white tumbled leather with a black lizard-textured mudguard. Gym Red accents settle on the midfoot overlay and an embroidered Jumpman logo atop the tongue. A lightweight Phylon midsole with Zoom Air cushioning provides a smooth and responsive ride.

name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low TD 'Space Jam'
story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low TD ‘Space Jam’ takes inspiration from the sleek AJ11 of the same name, which debuted in movie theaters in 1996 before hitting store shelves in 2000. The upper is built with black ballistic mesh and fortified with a tonal patent leather mudguard. Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and back heel. A crisp white finish is applied to a cushy foam midsole. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole yields durable traction.

name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low 'Space Jam'
story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘Space Jam’ is based on the high-top AJ11 of the same name, featuring a black ballistic mesh upper with a tonal patent leather mudguard. Rope laces feed through webbing eyelets for a secure fit, while the back heel is marked with a stylized ‘23’ and classic Jumpman branding. Anchoring the sneaker is a white Phylon midsole, fitted with full-length Air-sole cushioning and an exposed carbon fiber plate. A translucent rubber outsole utilizes herringbone traction pods for superior grip.

name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low GS 'Space Jam'
story: Built for big kids, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low GS ‘Space Jam’ takes inspiration from the coveted AJ11 release from 2000. Rope laces feed through webbing eyelets to secure an upper crafted from black ballistic mesh with a tonal patent leather mudguard. ‘23’ is printed on the heel tab, directly above an embroidered Jumpman logo in Varsity Royal. The low-top is mounted on a white Phylon midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low PS 'Space Jam'
story: Made for little kids, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low PS ‘Space Jam’ showcases the same sleek design worn by Michael Jordan in his 1996 cinematic debut. A stealthy black finish is executed on the upper, built with ballistic mesh and a shiny patent leather mudguard. Embroidered on the back heel is a royal blue Jumpman logo for a discreet pop of color. A white foam midsole offers lightweight cushioning with each step, while a translucent rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Green Glow
Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'Military Blue' 2024
story: The 2024 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro TD ‘Military Blue’ brings back an OG colorway in time for the classic silhouette’s 35th anniversary. True to the original, the upper features off-white leather construction with quarter panel netting and TPU support wings. Military Blue lands on the upper and lower eyelets, along with a heel tab marked with Nike Air branding. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a two-tone foam midsole, reinforced underfoot by a herringbone-traction outsole.

name: Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Military Blue' 2024
story: The 2024 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Military Blue’ brings back a coveted OG colorway of the legacy silhouette. Smooth off-white leather is utilized on the upper, featuring quarter panel netting and a tonal nubuck forefoot overlay. A vibrant blue Jumpman logo adorns the woven tongue tag, matching the molded eyelets and a back tab marked with Nike Air branding. The sneaker rides on a lightweight polyurethane midsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning in the forefoot and a visible Air bag in the heel.

name: Air Jordan 4 Retro GS 'Military Blue' 2024
story: Made for big kids, the 2024 reissue of the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS ‘Military Blue’ brings back one of the four OG colorways of the classic silhouette. The off-white leather upper is equipped with TPU support wings and breathable quarter panel netting. Bright blue accents make their way to molded eyelets, a woven Jumpman tongue tag, and a back tab embellished with Nike Air branding. The lightweight polyurethane midsole features a blue topline and exposed Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

name: Air Jordan 4 Retro PS 'Military Blue' 2024
story: The 2024 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS ‘Military Blue’ brings back an OG colorway in a scaled-down build made for little kids. Constructed from off-white leather, the upper features signature AJ4 details, including quarter panel netting and TPU support wings. A vibrant blue Jumpman logo graces the woven tongue tag, matching the molded eyelets and a back tab marked with Nike Air branding. A two-tone foam midsole is supported underfoot by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS 'Green Glow'
story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS ‘Green Glow’ blends white side panels with a black forefoot overlay and matching black Swoosh. Mint green accents land on the perforated toe box, heel overlay and collar flap, marked with the retro Wings logo on the lateral side. A woven Nike Air tag decorates the breathable nylon tongue. The high-top rests on a rubber cupsole, featuring white sidewalls and a bright green rubber outsole.

name: Jordan Tatum 2 Vortex
story: Representing one of the debut colorways of Jayson Tatum’s sophomore signature shoe, the Jordan Tatum 2 ‘Vortex’ takes inspiration from the NBA athlete’s calm demeanor under pressure. Textured textile and foam pods are strategically placed throughout the mint green textile upper and lightweight foam midsole, featuring a full-length Air Strobel unit for impact protection. Underfoot, the rubber outsole utilizes a modified herringbone traction pattern for multi-directional grip.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Craft Ivory
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Craft - Sea Glass’ arrives with a mixed-material upper, featuring an ivory leather base with pale green suede overlays and a color-matched Swoosh. Reflecting the design of the original AJ1 from 1985, the high-top is branded with a Nike tongue tag and the iconic Wings logo on the lateral collar flap. An aged off-white finish is applied to the rubber midsole, which houses an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated within a lightweight polyurethane wedge.

name: Jordan 9 Retro Powder Blue (2024)
story: The 2024 edition of the Air Jordan 9 Retro ‘Powder Blue’ brings back an OG colorway in honor of the shoe’s 30th anniversary. A speed lacing system secures the white leather upper, featuring stitched detailing on the side panels and a contrasting black mesh tongue. A powder blue interior sleeve matches the Air Jordan tongue tag and the molded Jumpman emblem that adorns the heel. Underpinning the sneaker is a polyurethane midsole, built with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and painted sidewalls in Carolina blue.

name: Jordan 3 Retro Green Glow
story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Green Glow’ adds brilliant flashes of color to a neutral design that calls to mind the OG ‘Black Cement’ colorway. The upper features tumbled black leather with grey elephant print detailing on the eyestay, toe cap and heel overlay. Vivid green accents settle on the upper and lower eyelets, along with the raised Jumpman logo that adorns the back tab. A polyurethane midsole packs a visible Air-sole unit in the heel for lightweight cushioning.

name: Air Jordan 3 Retro PS 'Green Glow'
story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 3 Retro PS ‘Green Glow’ dresses the classic silhouette in an OG-inspired design with vibrant pops of color. Black tumbled leather is deployed on the upper, contrasted by grey elephant print overlays at the forefoot, heel, and eyestay. The neutral tones are offset by molded eyelets in a mint green finish. A color-matched Jumpman logo adorns the tongue and back heel. The sneaker rides on a white foam midsole, accented with a wraparound splash of black and supported by a durable rubber outsole.

name: Air Jordan 3 Retro GS 'Green Glow'
story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 3 Retro GS ‘Green Glow’ brings fluorescent pops of color to an OG-inspired design that recalls the iconic ‘Black Cement’ release from 1988. The upper features black tumbled leather with grey elephant print overlays at the forefoot, heel and eyestay. Mint green accents make their way to the upper and lower eyelets, as well as Jumpman branding hits at the tongue and back heel. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a two-tone polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel.

name: Air Jordan 3 Retro TD 'Green Glow'
story: Scaled down for little feet, the Air Jordan 3 Retro TD ‘Green Glow’ uses the OG Black Cement colorway as a creative jumping-off point. The upper features black tumbled leather with grey elephant print overlays along the forefoot, heel, and eyestay. Fluorescent green accents stand out on the upper eyelets, matching the Jumpman branding hits that appear on the tongue and back heel. A foam midsole offers lightweight cushioning with each step, while a rubber outsole provides reliable traction.

name: Jordan 4 Retro Metallic Gold (Women's)
story: The Women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Metallic Gold’ delivers a pristine colorway of the legacy silhouette. A subtle off-white finish is executed on the smooth leather upper, featuring breathable quarter panel netting and metallic gold eyelets. Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and molded heel tab. A color-matched polyurethane midsole packs a visible Air-sole unit in the heel for lightweight cushioning. Underfoot, a cream-hued herringbone traction outsole provides optimal grip.

name: Jordan 5 Retro Olive (2024) (TD)
story: The 2024 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro TD ‘Olive’ draws from a popular Lifestyle Series colorway from 2006. Built for little feet, the classic silhouette features an olive green suede upper with breathable quarter panel netting. Contrasting orange accents land on the interior lining, as well as the Jumpman branding hits found on the back heel and silver reflective tongue. The sneaker is mounted on an olive-hued foam midsole with orange shark tooth detailing.

name: Jordan 5 Retro Olive (2024) (PS)
story: The 2024 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro PS ‘Olive’ brings back an archival Lifestyle Series colorway for little kids. Originally released in 2006, the legacy silhouette sports an olive suede upper with tonal molded eyelets and ventilated quarter panel netting. Orange textile lines the padded collar, matching the embroidered Jumpman logos that adorn the back heel and silver reflective tongue. A final splash of orange can be found on the speckled shark tooth detailing that enlivens the foam midsole.

name: Jordan 5 Retro Olive (2024) (GS)
story: Made for big kids, the 2024 reissue of the Air Jordan 5 Retro GS ‘Olive’ revives a Lifestyle Series colorway from Jordan Brand’s 2006 archive. The olive suede upper features hallmark details of the AJ5, including lace locks, quarter panel netting and a silver reflective tongue. The latter is marked with an orange Jumpman logo, matching the interior lining and a second Jumpman icon embroidered on the back heel. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an Air-assisted polyurethane midsole, finished in an olive drab hue with orange shark tooth detailing. A translucent rubber outsole provides grippy traction underfoot.

name: Jordan 5 Retro Olive (2024)
story: The 2024 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Olive’ brings back a popular colorway from Jordan Brand’s 2006 Lifestyle Series. Crafted from textured suede in a muted olive green hue, the upper features tonal molded eyelets and breathable quarter panel netting. Contrasting orange accents make their way to the interior lining, as well as the Jumpman logo hits that decorate the back heel and reflective tongue. Orange shark-tooth detailing decorates the olive-hued polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Air-sole cushioning and reinforced by a translucent rubber outsole.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Dusted Clay (Women's)
Jordan Tatum 2 Momma's Boy
story: The Jordan Tatum 2 ‘Momma’s Boy’ celebrates the close relationship that Jayson Tatum shares with his mother. The NBA athlete’s sophomore signature shoe features textured foam and mesh pods in his mom’s favorite color — Nike’s signature neon Volt hue — as well as an allover print of her favorite flower, the white calla lily, throughout the white textile upper. In terms of performance, the low-top utilizes a lightweight foam midsole with a full-length Air Strobel unit for impact protection.

name: Jordan 5 Retro Lucky Green (Women's)
story: The Women’s Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Lucky Green’ showcases OG-inspired color blocking reminiscent of the ‘Fire Red’ release from 1990. The white leather upper features breathable quarter panel netting and a plush textile lining in a vibrant green hue. In addition to an embroidered ‘23’ on the lateral heel, branding elements include a Jumpman logo at the tongue and back heel. The sneaker rides on a lightweight polyurethane midsole, painted green with black shark tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit nestled in the heel. A translucent rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black White
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Black White 2.0’ showcases an essential two-tone finish in classic ‘Bred’ color blocking. The high-top dons a smooth leather upper, featuring a black base with contrasting white accents on the toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar overlay. The latter is marked with a black Wings logo, while a woven Nike Air tag embellishes the nylon tongue. Encapsulated Air-sole cushioning enhances the rubber cupsole, which pairs white sidewalls with a black outsole.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black White (PS)
story: Offered in preschool sizing, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS ‘Black White 2.0’ outfits the iconic silhouette in a simplistic two-tone leather upper. The color blocking mirrors the original ‘Bred’ colorway, highlighted by a pitch-black base with contrasting hits of white on the toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar flap. Branding elements include a woven Nike tongue tag and a Wings logo imprinted on the lateral ankle. Undergirding the sneaker is a standard rubber cupsole, featuring white sidewalls and a durable black outsole.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black White (GS)
story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS ‘Black White 2.0’ showcases an elemental two-tone design in classic ‘Bred’ color blocking. Smooth leather is utilized on the upper, featuring black paneling with contrasting white accents on the toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar flap. OG-inspired accents include a woven Nike Air tag atop the nylon tongue and a Wings logo stamped in black on the lateral ankle. Lightweight cushioning is provided by an Air-sole unit nestled in the heel of the textured white midsole, supported underfoot by a durable black rubber outsole.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black White (TD)
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG TD ‘Black White 2.0’ delivers a neutral two-tone colorway of the classic silhouette for little feet. Rendered in familiar ‘Bred’ color blocking, the leather upper features a solid black base, contrasted by white accents on the toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar flap. The iconic Wings logo appears on the lateral ankle, while a woven Nike tag sits atop a lightly padded nylon tongue. A sturdy rubber cupsole, using the stitched sidewall construction of the original AJ1, anchors the high-top.

name: Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined
story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Bred Reimagined’ makes over the classic silhouette with a black leather upper, replacing the nubuck build of the original 1989 release. Heritage details include quarter panel netting, grey molded eyelets, and Nike Air branding on the heel tab. Atop the tongue, a woven Flight tag displays a crimson Jumpman logo. The mid-top is mounted on a lightweight polyurethane midsole, fitted with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning in the forefoot and an exposed Air unit in the heel. Underfoot, a pre-distressed rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for superior grip.

name: Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined (PS)
story: Offered in pre-school sizing, the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS ‘Bred Reimagined’ brings back the iconic colorway with a black leather upper, replacing the nubuck construction of the original. The legacy silhouette features breathable quarter panel netting and leather support wings topped with Cement Grey eyelets. A red Jumpman logo embellishes the tongue, while Nike Air branding on the heel tab delivers an OG touch. The sneaker rides on a cushy foam midsole, supported underfoot by an aged herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

name: Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined (GS)
story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS ‘Bred Reimagined’ treats the legacy silhouette to a material makeover, highlighted by a black leather upper that replaces the traditional nubuck build of the original. OG details remain intact, including Cement Grey accents on the textile lining and molded eyelets. Nike Air branding adorns the heel tab, while a crimson Jumpman logo graces the woven Flight tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel.

name: Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined (TD)
story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro TD ‘Bred Reimagined’ revives the classic colorway with an updated black leather upper, replacing the nubuck build of the original. Cement Grey accents land on the eyelets and interior lining, while a crimson Jumpman on the tongue provides a contrasting burst of color. Nike Air branding decorates the heel tab for an OG-inspired flourish. The sneaker rests on a lightweight foam midsole, reinforced by an aged herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High 85 OG Metallic Burgundy
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High ‘85 OG ‘Metallic Burgundy’ brings back an OG colorway from 1986. Built with the higher-cut collar and wider toe box of the silhouette’s original release, the foundational sneaker makes use of a white leather upper with contrasting Team Red accents. The rich pops of color land on the padded collar and the shoe’s branding elements, including the Swoosh, Nike Air tongue tag, and the Wings logo stamped on the lateral ankle. Anchoring the high-top is a durable rubber cupsole, featuring white sidewalls and a burgundy outsole.

name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High '85 OG TD 'Metallic Burgundy'
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High ‘85 OG TD ‘Metallic Burgundy’ brings back an archival colorway for the first time. The high-top makes use of a smooth white leather upper, contrasted by burgundy accents on the signature Swoosh and padded collar. The iconic Wings logo decorates the lateral collar, while Nike branding appears on the tongue tag and sockliner. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable rubber cupsole, featuring white sidewalls and a grippy burgundy outsole.

name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Trophy Room Away
story: The Trophy Room x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP ‘Away’ delivers a color-flipped take on the iconic ‘Black Toe’ AJ1. A black embroidered Swoosh adorns the white leather upper, contrasted by a red forefoot overlay in satiny textile. The latter is accented with a tonal embroidered Trophy Room logo, while a woven Nike tag graces the tongue. An embossed Wings logo in a metallic gold finish shines on the black textile back tab. The low-top rests on a vintage off-white midsole, supported underfoot by a crimson rubber outsole.

name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Trophy Room Home
story: The Trophy Room x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP ‘Home’ takes inspiration from Michael Jordan’s Fleer rookie card. A Trophy Room exclusive, the low-top makes use of a white textile upper with a color-matched embroidered Swoosh. A forefoot overlay in red leather features contrasting yellow and blue trim on the edges and a tonal Trophy Room logo on the lateral side. Black woven textile is utilized on the heel overlay and back tab, marked with an embossed Wings logo in metallic gold. Anchoring the sneaker is a rubber cupsole, highlighted by crisp white sidewalls and a grippy red outsole.

name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG TD 'Metallic Gold'
story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG TD ‘Metallic Gold’ dresses the iconic silhouette in a white leather upper, enlivened by gilded accents on the padded collar, signature Swoosh and Wings logo. Nike branding embellishes the woven tongue tag and sockliner. The high-top is mounted on a rubber cupsole that pairs textured white sidewalls with a gum rubber outsole, featuring a traction pattern designed to grip the hardwood in all directions.

name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS 'Metallic Gold'
story: Offered in preschool sizing, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS ‘Metallic Gold’ dons a white leather upper with a gilded finish on the high-cut collar, signature Swoosh and iconic Wings logo. Heritage details include a perforated toe box and a woven Nike tag atop the breathable nylon tongue. The rubber cupsole is undergirded by a high-traction outsole in grippy gum rubber.

name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Metallic Gold (Women's)
story: The Women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Metallic Gold’ showcases a white leather upper with gilded accents on the Swoosh, high-cut collar, the Nike Air tag atop the tongue, and the Wings logo imprinted on the lateral ankle flap. The sneaker is mounted on traditional cupsole tooling, built with white sidewalls and an Air-sole unit encapsulated in a polyurethane wedge. Underfoot, a gum rubber outsole features a traction pattern designed to grip the hardwood in all directions.

name: Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Blue Grey'
story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Blue Grey’ dresses the classic silhouette in OG-inspired color blocking. Crisp white leather is utilized on the forefoot and dimpled overlays, while synthetic suede in a blueish grey hue wraps around the midfoot and heel. Branding elements take the form of a yellow Jumpman logo atop the tongue and the AJ13’s holographic eye embedded in the lateral collar. The sneaker rests on a lightweight Phylon midsole, fitted with springy Zoom Air units in the forefoot and heel. Underfoot, the panther paw outsole reveals herringbone traction pods and an exposed carbon fiber shank plate.

name: Air Jordan 13 Retro GS 'Blue Grey'
story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS ‘Blue Grey’ showcases OG-style color blocking. The upper combines a white leather base with dimpled white leather overlays and synthetic suede paneling in a blueish grey hue. A yellow Jumpman logo is embroidered on the tongue, while the AJ13’s holographic eye adorns the lateral collar. The sneaker rides on a lightweight Phylon midsole, featuring black pods that accentuate the panther paw outsole.

name: Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Blue Grey'
story: Offered in pre-school sizing, the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS ‘Blue Grey’ delivers an understated colorway of the legacy silhouette. In addition to smooth white leather on the forefoot, the upper utilizes dimpled white leather overlays and synthetic suede paneling in a neutral shade of blue-grey. An embroidered yellow Jumpman atop the tongue offers a contrasting pop of color, while the AJ13’s holographic eye shines on the lateral collar. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a Phylon midsole, featuring black pods that outline the shoe’s distinctive panther paw outsole.

name: Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Blue Grey'
story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro TD ‘Blue Grey’ brings OG-inspired color blocking to a compressed build made for little feet. The upper features dimpled white leather overlays and smooth white leather construction throughout the forefoot. Blueish grey synthetic suede extends from the midfoot and wraps around the heel. Jumpman branding in Yellow Ochre adorns the tongue, while the AJ13’s holographic eye appears on the lateral collar. Underfoot, a herringbone traction rubber outsole provides reliable grip.

name: Jordan 1 Mid Inspired by the Greatest Aquatone (GS)
Jordan 2 Retro Low Python
story: The Air Jordan 2 Retro Low ‘Python’ sports a smooth white leather upper, accented with a snakeskin overlay in tan and silver. An embossed Wings logo graces the tongue in a neutral grey finish, matching the textile collar lining and Nike-branded insole. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an off-white polyurethane midsole, fitted with an encapsulated Air-sole unit and reinforced by rubber outsole in two shades of grey.

name: Jordan 3 Retro Craft Ivory
story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro SE ‘Craft’ in ‘Ivory’ showcases a white leather upper with grey elephant print overlays at the forefoot and heel. A double-exposed Jumpman decorates the tongue, while a semi-translucent heel tab displays tonal Jumpman branding atop a printed Nike logo. The throwback silhouette rides on a matching white polyurethane midsole, featuring visible Air-sole cushioning and a subtle splash of cream coloring at the heel. A translucent rubber outsole delivers durable traction underfoot.

name: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE PS 'Take Flight'
Jordan 6 Retro Yellow Ochre
story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Yellow Ochre’ updates the championship silhouette in color blocking that recalls the OG ‘Carmine’ release. Constructed with a yellow nubuck base and white leather overlays, the upper features Jumpman branding on the neoprene lace cover and back heel. Contrasting black accents land on the molded back tab, interior lining and tongue, fitted with dual grip holes for easy on and off. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a polyurethane midsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning in the forefoot and a visible Air unit in the heel. A translucent rubber outsole provides grippy traction underfoot.

Air Jordan 2 Retro Low 'Year of the Dragon'
story: The Air Jordan 2 Retro Low ‘Year of the Dragon’ features a white leather upper with jade-colored molded eyelets and a scaly-textured midfoot overlay. The latter is outlined in metallic gold trim, matching the embossed Wings logo atop the tongue. Dark Team Red accents land on the interior lining and molded back tab. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a white polyurethane midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and supported by a two-tone rubber outsole in jade and burgundy.
